{
  "abstract": "Currently recommended control measures against sorghum stem borers are briefly reviewed. Successful methods applied in developed countries have been tested at research stations in developing countries and recommended to farmers in the semi-arid tropics. The extent of their use by farmers is assessed and farm-and sector-level constraints to adaptation are evaluated. An approach for farmer-oriented research on control methods is suggested.",
